0. API design
GET "/" with a shortURL parameter in the query string.
-> return longURL
GET "/" with a longURL parameter in the query string.
-> return shortURL

1. RESTful API design (Do I need REST?)
POST "/shortURL" with a shortURL parameter in the query string.
-> return 307 response with JSON in the body { "longURL" : "www.google.com" }
POST "/longURL" with a longURL parameter in the query string.
-> return 200 response with JSON in the body { "shortURL" : "0123E2" }

